A FORMER school principal (59) accused of raping a 15-year-old pupil appeared at the Lenyenye Magistrates Court yesterday. He is charged with rape. He allegedly went to the girl&rsquo;s school and called her out last Thursday. He told her that he had a message for her.Not knowing what the man had up his sleeve, the girl went with the man, who had asked her to get into his car.Limpopo police spokesman Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the man took the girl to his house at a village just outside Tzaneen in Limpopo. &ldquo;On arrival at the house he allegedly raped her. The victim went to the police and opened a case of rape,&rdquo; said Ngoepe. He said after learning that he was a wanted man the suspect handed himself over to the police.Ngoepe said the suspect was expected to appear again in the same court today for a bail application.&ldquo;Police investigations are still continuing,&rdquo; he said.